We were levels 56-60 mostly, and mostly /roleplay.  I'm not even sure how you came to a &quot;mostly 52-56&quot; figure... since out of the 17 of us present, only about 3 were not /roleplay (3 or so is not most when your total is 17).<br>
<br>
&quot;We perceived this much like a Trakanon or Lozidal raid. Whoever gets enough people to start clearing to Juggs with a magician in tow generally &quot;has the camp&quot; at Trakanon.&quot;<br>
<br>
But you did not do this this time... since we had 15+ and growing in the zone while you had only 3 and growing.  We were there first, you could plainly and easily see it.  Obviously, we were already &quot;clearing the way to Juggs&quot; while the rest (our mana in this situation) became present.  Why would you say that you perceive it like something, then not act on it as such?<br>
<br>
&quot;We figured, as long as their puller wasn't out swimming with Kalorek`Dar, and if we got ready first, he was as much ours to pull as anyone's.&quot;<br>
<br>
