&quot;In the end, we got a few &quot;thanks for trampling over us&quot; messages; at which we offered to share or possibly even back down next time if they wanted to communicate with us. I suppose since Kalorek`Dar takes such a small number of people to kill, it might not have been obvious that we were moving in on it too, but I'll ask anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
No... we didn't think you were moving in on him since there was only a hand full of you there when we were set and buffed, and just waiting on mana at that point.  Also, we let our guard down when we saw it was &quot;Vision&quot; as well and didn't rush to beat you to said target.  You only had a few people there, and in light of our joining of forces in Fear (for the broken golem) a short while back... we didn't think we'd have anything to fear from you, as in a made rush to beat each other to a target.  We figured you saw our force already there, and would have respectfully left it at that.  Didn't expect we'd have to race you at all... thinking you would have done exactly what we would have done in that situation, and left.<br>
<br>
Actually... we already had done that once to that very same mob that night before we started rallying forces.  Exiled Alliance tried him out with a very small force and failed.  Guild chat from our trackers was saying we should rally and get there before Exiled reformed and tried again.  I told them all to leave it alone, since Exiled was there already and was most likely going to give it another shot.  I would hate to have someone come in and take him from us while we were trying him... so I would never do it to another.... so everyone listened to me and didn't gather, leaving the dragon to XA.  I didn't want to take the mob from XA since there were there trying him at that moment, and we were not.<br>
<br>
Guild chat started up again about 10 minutes later saying that the Exiled Alliance people had left, and it didn't look like they were waiting around for more to come help them, nor attempting the fight again themselves.  That's when we mobilized.  No ones feet were there to step on anymore, so all was good to move in.  We ported in, began forming groups and buffing.  I noticed 3 Vision in the zone, but didn't even think twice about it and didn't worry at all since, like I said, I didn't think you'd race us to the spawn after seeing our larger force already present.  A mistake that won't happen again.<br>
<br>
14 of you total had piled in and pulled him almost immediately upon arriving while we were sitting there waiting for those blue bars to hit 100% again.  14 total when I did a &quot;/who Vision&quot; after hearing the answer &quot;we did&quot; to the question &quot;Who just killed Klor?&quot; anyway.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that you commited a crime... EQ rules of engagement state that who ever engages first gets said mob, no camps, etc etc.  Not saying you were wrong... but rude?  Yes.<br>
<br>
&quot;at which we offered to share or possibly even back down next time if they wanted to communicate with us.&quot;<br>
<br>
Communication is a TWO way street.  Who are YOU that WE have to communicate with YOU for communication to start?  We were there first, you could plainly see this, YOU should have communicated with US.  NOT the other way around.  If you were there first in force, then we would have either asked you if you were hitting him or we would have left the zone without even asking.  What's this about you coming into a zone, and if people don't communicate with YOU, you're just going to take the mob because they must not be after it?  You are not our masters, you are not our peers, we do not answer to you.  Respect goes both ways.... and I, as well as our whole guild, had respect for Vision.  You, unfortunatly don't have respect for us, as you did NOT open the line of communication to the force that was there first (us).<br>
<br>
This line right here:<br>
<br>
&quot;at which we offered to share or possibly even back down next time if they wanted to communicate with us. &quot;<br>
<br>
That's the only line that pisses me off.  You got to the target first because we let down our guard and didn't think we had to worry about racing you.  I could care less about the target at this point though.  That's not the issue anymore as far as I'm concerned.  It's the lack of respect towards us that this line above shows that has me pissed.  Just because you entered the zone doesn't mean that we have to start sending you tells.  You are not our masters.  Your people are not better than our people, your people are not &quot;above&quot; our people, you do not hold some sort of higher &quot;rank&quot; that we must salute, you are not &quot;worth&quot; more, you are not &quot;worth&quot; less... you are another group of adventurers on this server, just like us.  You entering the zone does not mean that we have to quickly bow down and open communication, like you're &quot;above&quot; opening it with us or something.  Superior attitudes really piss me off.  We were in force first and medding up to pull, we should not have to drop everything to start a line of communication with you, when you should have opened it with us first.<br>
<br>
By not opening up communication with us, it ensured us that you weren't there for a dragon (just 3 Vision that happen to be in Cobalt Scar at the time).  We didn't think we had anything to worry from you, since you saw us there first, and never got a hold of us asking if that's what we were in the zone for.  So we didn't rush the pull, nor look at /who again to see your force grow quickly.<br>
<br>
If you were deep in the Halls of Testing, and we entered the Halls and started crawling as well... how would you feel if we said <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, well we didn't know you were here already, since you didn't send us tells letting us know upon our arrival to the zone&quot;?  <br>
<br>
How would you like it if we just entered the Halls and started fighting, without getting a hold of you at all to find out where you were camped (as not to bump into one another)?<br>
<br>
That's exactly what you did to us in Cobalt Scar.  You saw us there first, but didn't ask as to what we were there for.  But you expected US to?  We had no idea you were going for dragon since you weren't there in force when we were.  Are we to check in with Vision to make sure it's &quot;okay&quot; to hunt at all tomarrow?  I don't think so.<br>
<br>
If I enter a zone, it is NOT the job of everyone present in the zone ahead of me to just magically know that I've arrived, and to start sending me tells informing me of the targets they're all doing.  It is not the job of every group in a zone to constantly do /who's and track every new person entering.  It's the responsability of the new person to the scene.  It's common sense.<br>
<br>
I don't want to hear talk of &quot;We'll work with you if you treat us with respect&quot; when you showed us none by saying we had to get a hold of you because you just graced the zone with your presence.<br>
<br>
I don't want to hear talk of &quot;and if you don't want to work with us, then we'll do our best to beat you to targets fairly and be humble about it when we don't&quot;, when YOU didn't want to work with US.<br>
<br>
It's pure bullshit, and frankly I'm suprised as hell hearing such a hypocritical statement:<br>
<br>
&quot;We'll work with you if you treat us with respect; and if you don't want to work with us, then we'll do our best to beat you to targets fairly and be humble about it when we don't.&quot;<br>
