Two issues here, I'll try to take them seperately.<br>
<br>
First, you keep saying you were there in force.  Numbers don't equate to readiness.  Having more people in a zone doesn't make you any more or any less ready to engage a target.  You say yourself that we had people in the zone while you were gathering.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Well, we were gathing too.  We just gathered the NECESSARY and READY force faster.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Second, as to you who has to ask who...  ...sadly it boils down to this:  If our two guild run into a similar situation, and there is no communication, then it is likely, based on previous events that Vision will end up winning the race.  If our two guilds run into a similar situation, and there <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> IS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> communication, unless you plan on holding a grudge, our guilds will probably end up working together.<br>
<br>
Compare that to us forming up for a mob that Eternal Wrath wants to kill.  Eternal Wrath need not, under any circumstance that I can imagine, ever send us a tell asking for our &quot;permission&quot; to do anything.  On several occasions, we've sent them tells asking to do things with them.  As a result of that, Vision has a nice working relationship with Eternal Wrath.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> [Obviously the comparision between DL &lt; Vision &lt; EW isn't quite linear, but it helps demonstrate my point.]</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
We're faced with two choices, (a) silently race Eternal Wrath and lose, or (b) open dialogs with them and participate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> when YOU didn't want to work with US.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is gonna sound harsh, but I want to keep the terms simple.  At present, it benefits YOU more than it benefits US for our guilds to work together.<br>
